To more quantitatively understand our experimental measurement of the gain spectrum in terms of the “four-band” model and the gain spectra calculated from Eq. (3), we need to determine the steady-state distributions of electrons, excitons, and trions using the well-known mass-action law3,39. For electron trions formed byX+e↔T−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
